May 17 2007 	More service; less buzz	Things I love about the Mercer:1. The location -- right in the heart of Soho, with lots of restaurants and shopping right outside your door.2. Service -- warm and very friendly, which shows that this hotel has settled into a comfortable, luxurious middle age. When the hotel was fairly new, I felt that the emphasis was on &quot;cool&quot; service, in all its various meanings. Now the staff rushes over with a smile. 3. The little luxuries -- an iPod player in your room, for example. Generous supplies of shampoo, etc. Plus a very comfortable bed and a wonderful shower.4. An inviting lobby -- a comfortable place for breakfast or a drink. Pleasant alcove with a computer for checking your e-mail.Things you may not love about the Mercer:1. The location -- you're right on a busy corner, with crowds outside day and night. The rooms are well soundproofed, but forget about opening your window (unless you have a courtyard room).2. The rooms -- the epitome of industrial chic when they were first done. Now they just look industrial: long and narrow (like a galley kitchen) with white walls and venetian blinds on the windows. Maybe time for an update? (N.B. I had a standard room)3. The shampoo, etc. -- the Mercer has been using the same brand for as long as I can remember. Time for a change?I'm sure I'll be back, though I wouldn't be disappointed to hear that they're making some changes around the edges.	
